Disk Forensics > [T9]: UserAssist Registry Key: Program Usage Insights

(4) UserAssist Registry key

This key in the registry stores information about programs that are frequently run by a specific user, as well as the last time the programs were executed and how many times the user ran them. The key is stored at "ntuser.dat: Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Explorer\UserAssist." It contains multiple subkeys in the form of GUID (the type of application). Popular GUIDs are "{CEBFF5CD-ACE2-4F4F-9178-9926F41749EA}" for executables and "{F4E57C4B-2036-45F0-A9AB-443BCFE33D9F}" for shortcuts.

You can use the "UserAssist" tool by Didier Stevens to extract information from the UserAssist key,

 

UserAssist Information

Or you can use the UserAssist plugin in Registry Explorer to parse the information.

Parsing UserAssist using Registry Explorer

By examining this key, you can gain insights into the programs that a specific user frequently runs on the system.
